# Adjectives Reference Content

Adjective agreement patterns - words that describe nouns and must match in gender, case, and number.

## Purpose

Show how adjectives follow the same patterns as articles and nouns. Once you know noun patterns, adjectives follow the same rules.

## Key Insight

Adjectives agree with their noun in gender, case, and number. The adjective ending follows the same pattern as nouns.

---

## Core Rule: Adjectives Copy the Noun

<insight name="agreement-rule" highlight="true">
<title>Match the article's gender and case</title>
<explanation>
Look at the article. The adjective uses the same gender, case, and number as the noun it describes.
</explanation>
<examples>
- ο καλός φίλος (all masculine nominative)
- τον καλό φίλο (all masculine accusative - drop the -ς)
</examples>
</insight>

---

## Word Order

<rule>
Greek adjectives usually come BEFORE the noun:
- ο καλός φίλος (the good friend)
- NOT: *ο φίλος καλός
</rule>

