## Main Paradigm: -ος, -η, -ο

<paradigm name="kalos" frequency="very common">
<pattern>-ος, -η, -ο</pattern>
<title>Standard adjectives</title>
<example>καλός / καλή / καλό = good</example>
<tip>Most adjectives follow this pattern. Masculine like -ος nouns, feminine like -η nouns, neuter like -ο nouns.</tip>

### Masculine
| Case | Singular | Plural |
|------|----------|--------|
| Nom  | καλός    | καλοί  |
| Acc  | καλό     | καλούς |
| Gen  | καλού    | καλών  |

### Feminine
| Case | Singular | Plural |
|------|----------|--------|
| Nom  | καλή     | καλές  |
| Acc  | καλή     | καλές  |
| Gen  | καλής    | καλών  |

### Neuter
| Case | Singular | Plural |
|------|----------|--------|
| Nom  | καλό     | καλά   |
| Acc  | καλό     | καλά   |
| Gen  | καλού    | καλών  |

</paradigm>

