## Other Adjective Patterns (Collapsible)

<section expandable="true" default="collapsed">

### Pattern: -ος, -α, -ο

<paradigm name="oraios" frequency="common">
<pattern>-ος, -α, -ο</pattern>
<title>Adjectives with -α feminine</title>
<example>ωραίος / ωραία / ωραίο = beautiful/nice</example>
<tip>When the stem ends in a vowel or ρ, the feminine uses -α instead of -η.</tip>

| Gender    | Singular | Plural |
|-----------|----------|--------|
| Masculine | ωραίος   | ωραίοι |
| Feminine  | ωραία    | ωραίες |
| Neuter    | ωραίο    | ωραία  |

</paradigm>

### Pattern: -ύς, -ιά, -ύ

<paradigm name="varys" frequency="less common">
<pattern>-ύς, -ιά, -ύ</pattern>
<title>Short adjectives</title>
<example>βαρύς / βαριά / βαρύ = heavy</example>
<tip>A smaller group including βαρύς (heavy), ελαφρύς (light), μακρύς (long), φαρδύς (wide).</tip>

| Gender    | Singular | Plural |
|-----------|----------|--------|
| Masculine | βαρύς    | βαρείς |
| Feminine  | βαριά    | βαριές |
| Neuter    | βαρύ     | βαριά  |

</paradigm>

</section>

